{
  "texts": [
    "Even if they have fewer users, smaller platforms can still propagate disinformation or enabling discrimination [153].",
    "So the VLOP categorization seems limited from a risk perspective, and may allow harmful practices to go undetected on smaller platforms or other private channels.Redress Limitations Absence of minimum harmonized standards for notice-and-action procedures (Code: NTD) in managing content removal disputes risks inconsistent, arbitrary handling of misinformation reports across Member States (Article 14) [169].",
    "Redress mechanisms introduce complaint processes but lack impartial review prior to speech restrictions, disregarding horizontal effect principles (Articles 17, 18) [107].",
    "As noted by [78], content moderation rules of the DSA-notice and takedown, trusted flaggers, dispute resolution, risk management systems-should be selectively expanded to apply directly to Generative AI developers and deployers.",
    "This might contribute in having problematic content to be flagged and blocked at the source, before proliferation."
  ]
}